snippet.textDisplay:
so many people seem to relate to Kourtney and seemgingly find her blameless in this fight. From what I saw, Kourtney made the fight between Kim ad Kendall about her, she yelled "I will literally kill you", she threw the water bottle at Kim and got up to fight her while Kim was seated on the ground. Many rationals and excuses for Kourtney while Kim and Khloe are the toxic ones. Over the last two seasons, Kim and Khloe have tried to have sit downs with Kourtney to try and reach her and each time Kourtney has verbally lashed out at them and then became sullen and disinterested when they rebutted. I wonder when does Kourtney become responsible for her words and actions? When they had those sit downs she could have started the conversation about leaving the show. Besides contracts she's not obligated to be on the show and I'm sure that if Kourtney had actually mentioned if she was disillusioned, in pain, or depressed her sisters would have responded to that. Rudeness, blaming and being dismissive will not get the response you want. It's good she's separating from the show. Would have been great to come to that conclusion before two mature women got into a brawl over nonsense.

Of course, it is reality tv which is primarily scripted so it could all be fake. I mean, Kourtney didn't fully quit she's taking a break from the show. lol.

snippet.textDisplay: Well in all honesty... This was very hard and sad to watch all at the same time. Starting with Kourtney I can see and felt her anger even through tv. And I'm not even sure if it's just anger or a mixed emotion all together. Kourtney can be kinda rude and shut down and not want to listen to anyone when something is being told or addressed and she does tend to kinda come off rude at time's. However Kim can be a totally JERK about rubbing it in about her daily life and about her work ethics. Which high five for her for being a hard working woman and knowing how to handle being a celebrity all at the same time but it is true she loves to throw comments all the time to Kourtney. I can see where this frustration can take it to another level of being annoyed. With Khloe I think she ended up bonding with Kim because Kourtney became a mother and Kim and Khloe could relate and party. So that's where it seems thing's took a lil turn in Kourtney and Khloe's relationship. I would say it maybe a little bit of a secretly a tad of jealousy coming from Kourtney. And that's why she feels the way she feels about Khloe because her feelings are hurt because her Khloe were like besties. It just so happened that day that Kourtney had already had enough and had her cup of tea over filled that day and Kim was the one that had it hand it to her. However... I truly applaud Kourtney for being the mother she is and loving and caring for her kid's like no other. She is a full blown mom and she actually enjoys it much more then having the celebrity life. Unlike Kim and Khloe I'd say they enjoy more of the spotlight and are ok with having cameras in on their daily lives and doing it all. Kim and Khloe are ok juggling the glam, cameras and being mother's. Kourtney is more of a private person and likes her personal space and that is perfectly fine. If Kourtney chooses to opted out from the celebrity everyday daily life there is not anything wrong with it. Kourtney probably feels to much pressure to try to keep up with them and she feels like those are her sisters and may feel like she has to live up to the Kardashian's name. At the end of the day they are all sister's and should all love each other and respect everyone's boundaries that they each have. They are all grown adults & mother's, And need to act like one and set a great example for their children. They are a very close family and they do share a lot but at the end of the day love one another. I personally myself lost my sister several year's back. And I can truly say I miss her so damn much and think about her ALL the time. I'd do anything to be able to have her back for at least one day to be able to have another sister day. We were very close and I'm not going to say we did not have our fall outs but my mom always raised us to love each other at the end of the day no matter what. So for those who do have a sister or brother you are blessed and if yall have a nice sibling relationship you are truly blessed because at a blink of an eye it call be gone just like that. Love each other because tomorrow is guaranteed. It was only us two and now I long for my sister and wish so badly that she would still be here. I see siblings together and admire what they have. You may not realize what you have until it's all gone. Stay blessed and love your family like no other. ❤

She just wants normalcy in her life and has never had that. I also think she feels like Kim has always had the spotlight and she needs support and some of that as well. Idk. I hope she gets some help.
